ble with Keplerian\nrotation. As the star probably rotates at about 70% of its critical velocity\nthe ejection of matter doesn't seems to be dominated by rotation. However, the\ndisk geometry and kinematics are similar to that of the previously studied\nquasi-critically rotating Be stars, namely Alpha Ara, Psi Per and 48 Per.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Jun 2011 08:53:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-28"}
